  "text": "The source of firm-level data is the Encuesta sobre Estatregias Empresariales (ESEE), an annual survey conducted by the Fundación SEPI. This provides detailed information on companies that have operated in the Spanish manufacturing sector since the launch of the survey in 1990. In the base year, all firms that employed more than 200 employees (large firms) were asked to participate while firms with 10 to 200 employees (SMEs) were surveyed according to a random sampling scheme. Participation rates reached approximately 70% of the population of large firms and close to 5% of the population of SMEs. The same selective sampling scheme was applied to each industry in the base year. In subsequent years, entry of newly created firms and recorded exits have maintained the initial sample properties. Using this data, Huergo and Jaumandreu (2004) study the influence on productivity growth of process innovation at different firm ages while [CITATION_1] explore how the relationship between productivity and entry into exporting is mediated by product and process innovation.",
  "correct_citation": {
